[3] Cholera - Tanzania (Handemi, Korogwe)
Date: Thu, 10 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promemdail.org>
Source: Guardian [edited]
<http://209.183.227.156/ipp/guardian/2005/03/10/34359.html>

Cholera kills 7 in Handeni, Korogwe
-------------------------------------
A cholera outbreak has killed 7 people and hospitalized 72 others in Tanga
Municipality and Handeni and Korogwe districts.
Tanga Regional Health Adviser Barthazar Ngoli said the casualties were
among 180 who contracted the disease since it surfaced in the areas on 25
Feb 2005.
He said 4 people died in Handeni District where the 1st new case of cholera
was recorded on 28 Feb 2005, adding that 35 patients had been admitted to
15 emergency treatment centers in various parts of the district.
Dr Ngoli named villages hit by the outbreak in the district as Kwamsala,
Kwamatuku, Kwamkonga, Kwamkono, Chanika, Zavuza, Mandera, Maili Kumi and
Segera. Other areas are Chang'ombe, Michungwani, Kwedizinga, Kabuku Ndani,
Kwaraguru, Kwamaganga, Kabuku Nje and Sindeni.
He said cholera had killed 3 people in Korogwe District since 25 Feb 2005.
The 3 were among 103 people who had contracted the disease in the district
to date. Emergency treatment centers had 35 patients as of Tue, 8 Mar
2005, he added. The centers have been opened at Kilole, Magoma, Halle,
Kerenge and Madaraka villages.
Cholera has also spread in almost all parts of Korogwe Town including
Kirikiri, Manundu Kati, Habitati, Majengo, National Housing, Mountain View,
Madaraka, Kambi ya Maziwa, Manzese, Old Korogwe, Kwamngumi, Nyumbu and
Mahuezanguru.
Dr Ngole said 2 patients were receiving treatment at Mikanjuni and Mwambani
villages in Tanga Municipality. He blamed the latest outbreak on local
residents' failure to observe cleanliness and simple guidelines that could
easily prevent the disease.
[Byline: Thobias Mwanakatwe]
